cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the task of surface normal estimation from RGB-D data. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for this task, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to the cs.CV category. 

The paper also involves the use of robotics (cs.RO) as it mentions the availability of commodity RGB-D cameras, which are commonly used in robotics applications. 

The paper proposes a novel fusion network with adaptive feature re-weighting, which involves the use of machine learning techniques such as loss functions and feature selection. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. 

Finally, the paper involves the task of scene understanding, which is related to the Graphics (cs.GR) category. However, since the paper primarily focuses on the use of deep learning techniques for surface normal estimation, it is less likely to belong to the cs.GR category compared to the other categories mentioned above.
